This piece features a 2 seater sofa and a 3 seater connected by a corner table and 2 incorporated side tables.

name: Wega 3300 Hifi Stereobar by Verner Panton
description:
This is one of our shop favourites!

Wega 3300 Hifi stereo system, with Dual 1218 record player. 

Designed in 1963 by Verner Panton, and built by Wega in 1973, this piece is rare as hen's teeth.
This is one for a true collector - or anyone with smashing style!

The unit is rectangular with rounded corners and consists of 2 sections. One level contains the radio and the other the record player. 
The whole unit is on casters and can be easily moved, although beware - it's a hefty 61 kilograms.

This model only ever came in 3 lacquered wood colours - Black, White and Orange. Here we have a white one, and it's the only Wega 3300 we have ever had the pleasure of seeing in the flesh.

The internal parts have just been fully reconditioned, for your listening pleasure :)

The original slogan for the HiFi was
"Das ist hifi-spitzentechnik in eigenwilliger, aber praktischer form"
which translates as "This is hifi-technology in unconventional but practical form".

True that.

name: Reclaimed Wood and Steel Industrial Shelving unit
Mechanics Wooden Storage Trays
description:
These were bought from a retiring mechanic, and were handmade in the 50's.
They were used in the one place for almost 60 years, until we found them!
Because they were used to store tools and parts there is some dirt and greasy patina - Which makes them look amazing!
The one in this photo was washed to look cleaner and the wood turned a nice light colour once all the years of workshop grease was gone, which also looks great. 
Your choice - Keep the grease, or use your own elbow grease to give them a fresh start!

name: 4 x Fler SC55 dining chairs with original vintage fabric
description:
The SC55 range was created by Fler in 1955, and these dining chairs are becoming increasingly rare.

This set is in great condition! 
1 has recently been reglued and stabilsed and the other 3 are yet to wobble.
The fabric is a beautiful chocolate brown velour, and is in excellent shape. Absolutely no need to recover these (unless you've got a new fabric in mind).

Fler was formed by Fred Lowen and Ernest Roddick in the early 1950's and they created some of the most influential designs of the Australian Mid Century Modern aesthetic.

The Fler SC55 dining chair is hard to find.. Unlike other mid century modern designs, you won't see this style pop up for sale very often - especially a set of 4.

These are a great buy for a collector.. And if you're not a collector - you can be assured you'll never lose money on this investment!

name: Christine Rosamond - Garden Child. 1975
description:
Rosamond first sold her work at a Los Angeles street Bazaar where her pieces were quickly snapped up. By the age of 25 Rosamond was a major player in the art world and one of few females to succeed in it. 

Her paintings, noted for their negative space, economy of line and purity of subject matter immediately struck a chord with the public. She became the most published artist in the world eclipsing the likes of Salvador Dali and Norman Rockwell yet her name is not nearly as well known as the artists' she surpassed in print.

name: 1950's Rocking Horse
description:
This rocking horse was built from a DIY pattern, that was available from hardware stores in the 50's.

Men (and some women) around the country would use the template to create the basic horse shape, and then customise to their liking, with different paint, eyes, hair, lacquer, etc.

This one, has a simple beauty, that highlights the construction in a really pleasing way.. I love this little horsey! A real one-of-a-kind!

name: Yellow Maya Desk Lamp
description:
"Brilliant Lighting" brand released the Maya lamp sometime in the early 80's I think.

Made in China, complete with a cute smiley face on the head of the lamp, this one is in great condition.

The 'aerials' on the neck of the lamp retract to 16cm at their smallest, and extend to 37cm at their tallest. Also the head and aerials are both adjustable to various angles. Handy!

The only blemishes are two small marks on the top of the lamp. You can see this on the last picture.

So rad!

name: Fler SC55 dining chair with original vintage fabric
description:
The SC55 range was created by Fler in 1955, and these dining chairs are becoming increasingly rare.

This one would make a beautiful chair for your office, sewing machine, or a boudoir seat.

Fler was formed by Fred Lowen and Ernest Roddick in the early 1950's and they created some of the most influential designs of the Australian Mid Century Modern aesthetic.

Their works were often awarded the Good Design Index's mark of approval, and are sought after still today.

name: 1960's Curved Chrome and Glass Side Table
1960's Yellow Swivel Chairs
description:
These are an awesome shape! They swivel with ease, and are in great condition for their age.

Seen in Mad Men, this style is so similar to the guest chairs in Donald Draper's office in Season 4 and 5!

name: 1970's Sandwich Saver
description:
Gorgeous original bright orange Kristaware sandwich saver.
Manufactured in Melbourne in the 1970's.

These are hard to come by nowadays, and so cute!

Good for small loaves of bread as well, when you're not serving club sandwiches.

name: Wire Fruit Bowl - Clement Meadmore style
description:
Wire fruit bowl from the 1950's, in the style of Clement Meadmore.
Simple and beautiful style.

The coated wire has some black that has rubbed off (as you can see in the photos) which adds the the great patina.

name: 1950's Meta Brand Hair Clipper
description:
Hair Clipper made in France, in original packaging.

The box has some staining on it and the clippers need sharpening and have some rust.

Great display piece, or with a small amount of work, they could be brought back to their former glory!

name: American School Clock
description:
American Time & Signal Clock, commonly found in American high schools across the country in the 1970's and 80's.

I picked up this one in California, and brought it all the way home to Melbourne.

I'd say it would be hard to find another one like it here!

This clock needs a new Australian plug, but all of the wiring is in good condition, so this will be a relatively easy job for the new owner.

name: 1950's Curved Blondewood Footstool
description:
Beautifully handmade footstool, from blonde wood and circa 1950's.

This is perfect for resting a cup of coffee on (trust me) and is lovely by a sitting chair, or used as a bedside table.

It's one of a kind!

name: Vintage Shoe Brush
description:
This shoe brush is in excellent condition, with a lovely brass zippered enclosure for your accessories.

Perfect for that hard to buy for man or woman who loves beautiful old things.

It has never been used, either! Half your luck!
